data.title: Henry V
data.meta_description: Henry V (1989) starring Kenneth Branagh, Derek Jacobi, Brian Blessed and directed by Kenneth Branagh.
data.text: King Henry V of England (Sir Kenneth Branagh) is insulted by King Charles VI of France (Paul Scofield). As a result, he leads his army into battle against France. Along the way, the young King must struggle with the sinking morale of his troops and his own inner doubts. The war culminates at the bloody Battle of Agincourt.
